OL,3,CJersey children more vulnerable to
OL,4,Charm online, report finds
OL,6,FThe law makes companies legally
OL,7,Fresponsible for online safety, but
OL,8,FJersey's decision not to opt in means
OL,9,Fthere is no dedicated legislation to
OL,10,Fprotect the island's children online.
OL,12,FWhat did the review find?
OL,14,FThe review - which was written after a
OL,15,Fseries of public hearings and informed
OL,16,Fby submissions from parents, childcare
OL,17,Fprofessionals, and young people
OL,18,Fthemselves - made 63 findings and 38
OL,19,Frecommendations.
OL,21,FThe panel's key findings include:
