OL,3,CJersey children more vulnerable to
OL,4,Charm online, report finds
OL,6,FWith no legislation dictating safety
OL,7,Fmeasures such as network filtering by
OL,8,Finternet service providers and age
OL,9,Fverification for certain websites,
OL,10,FDeputy Curtis fears that "children in
OL,11,FJersey can see anything online".
OL,13,F"Children are curious", she says, "and
OL,14,Fan eight or nine year old just
OL,15,Fsearching different items would
OL,16,Fstumble across porn, murder,
OL,17,Fterrorism, anything.
