OL,3,CJersey children more vulnerable to
OL,4,Charm online, report finds
OL,6,F"There are no protections around
OL,7,Fcyberbullying, misinformation, self-
OL,8,Fharm and suicide being promoted
OL,9,Fonline, so there's no accountability
OL,10,Ffor this in Jersey at all."
OL,12,FEmily Jennings, parent and campaigner
OL,13,Ffor the pressure group Smartphone Free
OL,14,FChildhood, welcomes the idea of urgent
OL,15,FGovernment action.
OL,17,F"This really is an urgent issue,
OL,18,Fbecause none of us want our children
OL,19,Fto come to harm, and we don't want to
OL,20,Flose another child to suicide, self-
OL,21,Fharm, or violence", she says.
