OL,3,CJersey children more vulnerable to
OL,4,Charm online, report finds
OL,6,FEmily believes children are at risk
OL,7,Fonline in two ways.
OL,9,FPrimarily, through exposure to harmful
OL,10,Fcontent such as violence, misogyny,
OL,11,Fextremism, suicide, self-harm, or
OL,12,Fdangerous dares and challenges.
OL,14,F"There is also harm from addictive
OL,15,Fdesign", she adds, where "children are
OL,16,Ffinding themselves drawn into using
OL,17,Ftechnology and not able to control
OL,18,Ftheir usage anymore".
