OL,3,CJersey children more vulnerable to
OL,4,Charm online, report finds
OL,6,FAlongside legislation, she believes
OL,7,Fparents, teachers, and other
OL,8,Fstakeholders need to take collective
OL,9,Fresponsibility for the protection of
OL,10,Fchildren in online spaces.
OL,12,F"It's everyone's responsibility",
OL,13,FEmily explains.
OL,15,F"The parent voice is really crucial
OL,16,Fbecause they're the ones on the
OL,17,Fground, seeing their children using
OL,18,Fthis tech, picking up the pieces when
OL,19,Fthey have cyber trauma, and trying to
OL,20,Fhelp them manage the use of some of
OL,21,Fthis addictive tech."
