OL,3,CJersey children more vulnerable to
OL,4,Charm online, report finds
OL,6,FThese include: the creation of a cross-
OL,7,Fministerial working group to tackle to
OL,8,Fproblem of online safety for children;
OL,9,Fdigital literacy programmes in
OL,10,Fschools; the review of parental
OL,11,Fcontrols provided by local
OL,12,Ftelecommunications suppliers; the
OL,13,Frestriction of mobile phone use in
OL,14,Fschools; and the development of
OL,15,Flegislation to tackle intimate image
OL,16,Fabuse, stalking and harassment
OL,17,Foffences, and illegal content.
